The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 The CAB will host a 14-day physical conditioning-cum-mental toughness camp for the Bengal Ranji players at the Eden from July 20. While former South African trainer Adrian Le Roux will supervise the physical conditioning camp, former India captain Sourav Ganguly will conduct the mental toughness programme. The second camp will be held in August.      
	Bengal will play in the Plate division this year.          
	 Nabagram Vidyapith of Hoogly emerged champion in the under-17 category of the 3rd All Bengal Cosco School Badminton tournament beating Naihati Narendra Vidyaniketan in the final at Khudiram Anushilan Kendra on Wednesday. Adarsha Balika clinched the under-17 girls title.           
	CRICKET: J.C. Mukherjee semi-final at Eden from 10am                                                                                                                                                                     
